<task id="002" project="file-preview-dialog-with-auth-enhancements">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement Token Acquisition Strategies</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>auth, shared-package, token-acquisition</tags>
    <estimate>3-4 hours</estimate>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Implement the 5-strategy token acquisition cascade in @spaarke/auth</goal>
    <context>
      Token acquisition must try strategies in priority order: parent bridge (iframe token sharing),
      in-memory cache, Xrm platform (frame-walk to find Xrm.Utility.getGlobalContext), MSAL ssoSilent,
      and MSAL popup as last resort. This cascade ensures tokens are acquired with minimal user
      disruption. The existing bffAuthProvider.ts in LegalWorkspace implements parts of this logic
      but is tightly coupled to that solution. This task extracts and generalizes the pattern.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST be React 16/17 compatible per ADR-022
      - MUST NOT import PCF-specific APIs (ComponentFramework.*) per ADR-012
      - Xrm frame-walk MUST handle cross-origin errors gracefully
      - MSAL strategies MUST use @azure/msal-browser v3.x PublicClientApplication
      - Each strategy MUST return ITokenResult or null (no throwing on expected failures)
      - Strategy chain MUST stop at first successful result
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/services/bffAuthProvider.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/msal-client.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/token-caching.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/auth.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read bffAuthProvider.ts to understand existing token acquisition logic and strategy ordering</step>
    <step>Read MSAL client pattern from .claude/patterns/auth/msal-client.md</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/ directory</step>
    <step>Define ITokenStrategy interface in strategies/types.ts with acquire(scopes: string[]): Promise&lt;ITokenResult | null&gt;</step>
    <step>Implement BridgeStrategy in strategies/BridgeStrategy.ts - reads token from parent iframe bridge</step>
    <step>Implement CacheStrategy in strategies/CacheStrategy.ts - reads from in-memory token cache with expiry check</step>
    <step>Implement XrmStrategy in strategies/XrmStrategy.ts - frame-walks to find Xrm.Utility.getGlobalContext, acquires token via platform API</step>
    <step>Implement MsalSilentStrategy in strategies/MsalSilentStrategy.ts - uses MSAL ssoSilent with login hint</step>
    <step>Implement MsalPopupStrategy in strategies/MsalPopupStrategy.ts - uses MSAL acquireTokenPopup as fallback</step>
    <step>Create SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts that chains all 5 strategies in priority order and returns first successful result</step>
    <step>Export all strategies and SpaarkeAuthProvider from index.ts</step>
    <step>Verify build with tsc --noEmit</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/types.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/BridgeStrategy.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/CacheStrategy.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/XrmStrategy.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/MsalSilentStrategy.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/strategies/MsalPopupStrategy.ts</output>
    <output>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 5 token acquisition strategies implemented with consistent interface</criterion>
    <criterion>SpaarkeAuthProvider chains strategies in correct priority order</criterion>
    <criterion>XrmStrategy handles cross-origin frame-walk errors without throwing</criterion>
    <criterion>MSAL strategies use @azure/msal-browser v3.x PublicClientApplication</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compiles without errors</criterion>
    <criterion>Each strategy returns ITokenResult or null (no throwing on expected failures)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
